{
  "stem": "15197.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We didn't know exactly the date when, but we knew that it will take place.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And at that time, the fighters organization, the groups-- there were about 22 groups-- were already on alert.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And at that time, the communication was a little bit tighter and more often.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The uprising started the 19th of April, 1943.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I was on the Polish side.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We didn't know exactly when.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And at that time, we heard shooting and then we-- the few people on the Aryan side want to get into the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But the ghetto was surrounded more with German patrols and it was impossible to get-- even it was no smuggle, it was nothing.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I tried and I succeeded in getting in very close to the street which has the ghetto wall in the middle of the street.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "One side was in the ghetto and the other side was the Polish side.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There we have one Polish family, [POLISH], who was hiding two Jewish children.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I went up there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I didn't bribe the Ukranian who was on guard, but I just told him that I have my mother there and I have to see her and-- and you have to let me through as a Polish girl.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And finally, he let me through.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And at that time, I was staying overnight there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I saw how the ghetto was in flames, how the Jewish houses were burning and people were jumping from balcony.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I remember staying at the window and seeing the flames and Mrs.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[POLISH] constantly telling me, get away from the window, they will see you.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They will see you.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But how could I get away when the world which I was born and connected gets up in flame?",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
